# Image Analysis 

## Methodology

1. Make sure the file type is the file type that it states
2. Check the metadata through `exiftool` and use `strings` to look at all strings in image.
    - 



## Strings
*Use methods on garden.jpg, to follow along (Taken from PICOCTF)*

To view strings of an image do `strings` in linux and then the filename
Ex: `strings garden.png`

We can see at the bottom that it contains `picoCTF{more_than_m33ts_the_3y3a63b5b27}`
Alternatively you can just use an hex editor and view it that way.


